MVP OF AI-TO-AI MARKETPLACE

1.  MVP Goal
    A minimal prototype that only proves one thing:
    [An agent can discover another agent, request a task, recieve the result, and trigger payment automatically]

2.  Components
    ~ Component 1-Agent Registry
    This is the directory of all agents, and each agent publishes its capabilities. Database options(PostgreSQL, MongoDB). Functions needed: register_agent(), update_agent(), search_agent().
    {
    "agent_id": "data-summarizer-01",
    "endpoint": "https://agent-url/api/run",
    "capabilities": ["summarize_text", "extract_keywords"],
    "price_per_task": 0.01,
    "avg_latency": 3,
    "reputation_score": 4.7
    }

    ~ Component 2-Task Broker
    This service matches tasks with agents. The broker searches registry, ranks agents by reputaion score + price, sends request to the best agent.
    {
    "task": "summarize_text",
    "input": "large research article",
    "budget": 0.02
    }

    ~ Component 3- Agent Communication protocol
    All agents must use the same request format
    {
    "task_id": "9834",
    "task_type": "summarize_text",
    "input_data": "...",
    "callback_url": "https://broker/api/result"
    }

    ~ Component 4-Verification Layer
    Before payment is released, another system verifies the output. For simple tasks, verification might be automated.
    Verification methods:
    rule-based validation
    secondary AI check
    checksum validation for deterministic tasks

    ~ Component 5-Payment Layer
    After verification, escrow-execute-verify-pay. This layer records the transaction.
    task_id: 9834
    payer_agent: research-agent-01
    worker_agent: summarizer-agent-01
    amount: $0.01
    status: paid

3.  Basic System Architecture

         Agent Registry
               |
         Task Broker
               |
         ______|_________
        |                |
        Worker Agent    Verifier Agent
        |_________________|
               |
            Payement Layer
